<paragraph blockId="39.[242,1474,1375,1434]" pageId="39" pageNumber="138">ETYMOLOGY. — The Latin participle ‘scansus’ (from scando) means climbed, reached the top, as the species seems to be at home on higher mountain ranges.</paragraph>
